"{\"uid\": \"si.com-olympics-2024-05-02-katie-ledecky-planning-compete-2028-olympics\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"What does American swimming icon Katie Ledecky have left to prove?\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 66, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10, \"end\": 18, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9998663902473495, \"rank\": 0.00011209451297926192, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 33, \"end\": 46, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katie Ledecky\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Not much.\", \"from\": 67, \"to\": 76, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Her medal record is eye-popping: seven Olympics golds and three Olympic silvers to go with 21 world golds and five silvers.\", \"from\": 78, \"to\": 201, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Her medal record\", \"from\": 78, \"to\": 94}, {\"ngram\": \"seven Olympics golds\", \"from\": 111, \"to\": 131}, {\"ngram\": \"three Olympic silvers\", \"from\": 136, \"to\": 157}, {\"ngram\": \"21 world golds\", \"from\": 169, \"to\": 183}, {\"ngram\": \"five silvers\", \"from\": 188, \"to\": 200}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She owns the world long- and short-course records in the 800-meter freestyle and 1500-meter freestyle.\", \"from\": 202, \"to\": 304, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the world long- and short-course records\", \"from\": 211, \"to\": 251}, {\"ngram\": \"the 800-meter freestyle\", \"from\": 255, \"to\": 278}, {\"ngram\": \"1500-meter freestyle\", \"from\": 283, \"to\": 303}]}, {\"sentence\": \"No conversation attempting to rank the greatest North American athletes of the 21st century is complete without her.\", \"from\": 305, \"to\": 421, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 359, \"end\": 367, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9998663902473495, \"rank\": 0.00011209451297926192, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"No conversation\", \"from\": 305, \"to\": 320}, {\"ngram\": \"the 21st century\", \"from\": 380, \"to\": 396}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And yet, not only is Ledecky primed for another big Olympics this summer in Paris, she also indicated to NBC recently that she might not be done after that.\", \"from\": 423, \"to\": 579, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 499, \"end\": 504, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999566890863035, \"rank\": 4.3312789573467326e-05, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 528, \"end\": 531, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"score\": 0.9999980595071702, \"rank\": 1.6942504987230572e-06, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Ledecky\", \"from\": 444, \"to\": 451}, {\"ngram\": \"another big Olympics\", \"from\": 463, \"to\": 483}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The (2028) Olympics being in LA is very appealing.\", \"from\": 581, \"to\": 632, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The (2028) Olympics\", \"from\": 582, \"to\": 601}, {\"ngram\": \"LA\", \"from\": 611, \"to\": 613}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Not very many athletes get an opportunity to compete in a home Games,\\\" Ledeckysaid.\", \"from\": 633, \"to\": 716, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Not very many athletes\", \"from\": 633, \"to\": 655}, {\"ngram\": \"an opportunity\", \"from\": 660, \"to\": 674}, {\"ngram\": \"a home Games\", \"from\": 689, \"to\": 701}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I definitely at this point am planning on going through 2028... whether I compete in one event, multiple events, a relay, whatever.\\\"\", \"from\": 717, \"to\": 850, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this point\", \"from\": 734, \"to\": 744}, {\"ngram\": \"one event\", \"from\": 803, \"to\": 812}, {\"ngram\": \"a relay\", \"from\": 831, \"to\": 838}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ledecky turned 27 on St. Patrick's Day, and will be 31 by the time Los Angeles rolls around.\", \"from\": 852, \"to\": 944, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 877, \"end\": 884, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patrick_Drake\", \"score\": 0.6683183094991051, \"rank\": 0.4867582174832491, \"text\": \"Patrick\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patrick_Drake\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patrick_Drake\"}, {\"begin\": 919, \"end\": 930, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.99996682840464, \"rank\": 3.2943737000441395e-05, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Ledecky\", \"from\": 852, \"to\": 859}, {\"ngram\": \"the time\", \"from\": 910, \"to\": 918}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Only three women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094the United States's Dara Torres in 2000, the Netherlands' Inge de Bruijn in 2004, and West Germany's Ursula Happe in 1956\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094have ever won a swimming gold past the age of 30.\", \"from\": 945, \"to\": 1137, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 968, \"end\": 981, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.7260250814612328, \"rank\": 0.37736104067840964, \"text\"